    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect parameter order in fullwrite function calls\n\n### Summary\nThe `fullwrite` function in the RF simulator had its parameters reordered to improve clarity and prevent potential misuse. The original parameter order placed the file descriptor before the buffer pointer, which could lead to confusion when developers swapped similarly-typed parameters. This change modifies the function signature to place the buffer first, following common I/O conventions, and updates all calls accordingly.\n\nThis fix addresses an issue where incorrect argument order in function calls could cause unexpected behavior when writing data to sockets in the RF simulator.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/rfsimulator/simulator.c`: \n  - Modified `fullwrite` function signature to `fullwrite(void *_buf, int fd, ssize_t count, rfsimulator_state_t *t)`\n  - Updated calls to `fullwrite` to match new parameter order\n  - Minor formatting adjustments in configuration parameter definitions\n  - Fixed indentation in telnet command handling\n\n"
}